1
00:00:11,767 --> 00:00:13,200
I knew it!

2
00:00:13,267 --> 00:00:14,500
You're a traitor!

3
00:00:14,567 --> 00:00:16,767
I just want to surprise you.

4
00:00:16,833 --> 00:00:17,867
Don't fight.

5
00:00:17,933 --> 00:00:21,200
My gosh, you should talk
to your daughter.

6
00:00:21,267 --> 00:00:22,867
There's a possibility
that Jade is my daughter.

7
00:00:22,933 --> 00:00:26,333
This is one of the necklaces
that I gave the twins

8
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:28,033
before I gave them up
for adoption.

9
00:00:28,100 --> 00:00:31,000
But they can't be my sister!
Especially Olive!

10
00:00:31,067 --> 00:00:32,167
She's evil!

11
00:00:32,233 --> 00:00:33,467
We're both mothers here.

12
00:00:33,533 --> 00:00:35,500
We both suffered from losing
a child.

13
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:38,833
You should understand
what I'm going through.

14
00:00:38,900 --> 00:00:41,500
Why are you insisting that Olive
is your daughter?

15
00:00:41,567 --> 00:00:44,267
I thought we hated
that crazy woman?

16
00:00:44,333 --> 00:00:47,133
This came from our biological
mother.

17
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:51,567
That's the picture
I gave the person

18
00:00:51,633 --> 00:00:54,633
who handled your adoption.

19
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:35,667
I'm going to talk to Caloy
real quick.

20
00:01:35,733 --> 00:01:38,267
I'll ask him to buy
the cake you want.

21
00:01:39,233 --> 00:01:40,767
I'll be right back.

22
00:01:40,867 --> 00:01:42,333
Okay.

23
00:02:05,333 --> 00:02:09,500
To my children, when you read
this letter...

24
00:02:11,100 --> 00:02:13,500
I hope you'll understand

25
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:20,067
I gave you up so you can have
a better life.

26
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:23,967
Something I'm not able
to provide.

27
00:02:27,867 --> 00:02:29,767
I'm not a good mother.

28
00:02:32,433 --> 00:02:34,200
I'm weak.

29
00:02:34,267 --> 00:02:40,500
I can't withstand all
the beatings.

30
00:02:40,567 --> 00:02:44,833
That I hope you will never
experience.

31
00:02:44,900 --> 00:02:48,033
I don't want you to starve,

32
00:02:48,133 --> 00:02:50,633
to be in pain,
to be in a hostile environment.

33
00:02:50,700 --> 00:02:54,567
I want you to have proper
nutrition

34
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:57,500
and be raised with so much love.

35
00:02:57,567 --> 00:03:01,433
I will do anything for you
to be happy.

36
00:03:03,267 --> 00:03:05,333
Please forgive me.

37
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:12,267
I love you so much.

38
00:03:13,867 --> 00:03:20,900
How come you know what
the letter says?

39
00:03:24,167 --> 00:03:26,067
Because I wrote that letter.

40
00:03:29,933 --> 00:03:33,933
I gave that letter to the person
who handled your adoption.

41
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:48,800
Jade,

42
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:55,567
I'm your mother.

43
00:03:55,667 --> 00:03:57,300
I'm your mom.

44
00:04:25,867 --> 00:04:27,367
Look so good!

45
00:04:27,467 --> 00:04:28,733
Take a bite, Mommy.

46
00:04:34,567 --> 00:04:38,067
Go on. Try it, too.

47
00:04:38,133 --> 00:04:40,233
I'm okay, Mom.

48
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:42,800
I want to make it up to you.

49
00:04:47,767 --> 00:04:52,367
Mommy, are we on good terms now?

50
00:04:52,433 --> 00:04:55,933
Have you forgiven me for
everything that I've done?

51
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:59,267
Of course, Mookie.

52
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:02,033
What makes you think
that we're not okay?

53
00:05:03,700 --> 00:05:06,400
I feel guilty.

54
00:05:06,467 --> 00:05:12,667
I feel bad
because I let Mommy...

55
00:05:12,733 --> 00:05:15,333
I mean, Emma brainwashed me.

56
00:05:17,133 --> 00:05:22,700
That's why I'll never get tired
of apologizing.

57
00:05:24,867 --> 00:05:28,433
And I will also never get tired
of forgiving and loving you,

58
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:29,767
Mookie.

59
00:05:29,833 --> 00:05:33,767
Promise me you'll never
leave me.

60
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:37,500
Because I can't bear
to lose you, Mookie.

61
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:39,267
Promise?

62
00:05:41,900 --> 00:05:43,833
I'll never leave you, Mommy.

63
00:05:46,833 --> 00:05:47,900
Promise.

64
00:05:55,100 --> 00:05:57,400
Wait..

65
00:05:59,633 --> 00:06:01,067
wait a minute.

66
00:06:02,367 --> 00:06:03,667
Let me think...

67
00:06:03,733 --> 00:06:09,167
how is it possible
that you're my mom?

68
00:06:09,267 --> 00:06:13,233
How did that happen?

69
00:06:13,300 --> 00:06:15,600
You have to believe me.

70
00:06:15,667 --> 00:06:19,367
Even I'm confused.

71
00:06:19,433 --> 00:06:24,600
I didn't expect this to happen.
I didn't know how this happened.

72
00:06:24,667 --> 00:06:26,267
Wait...

73
00:06:26,333 --> 00:06:28,333
let me think.

74
00:06:29,467 --> 00:06:35,233
Earlier, you kept asking
me personal questions.

75
00:06:35,300 --> 00:06:39,667
About me, about my family.
And now...

76
00:06:45,433 --> 00:06:46,733
It's you?

77
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:47,867
You're...

78
00:06:49,067 --> 00:06:55,867
You're my mom?

79
00:06:55,933 --> 00:06:57,867
That's right, sweetie.

80
00:06:57,933 --> 00:07:05,133
Your adoptive parents
were doctors, right?

81
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:09,700
The couple who adopted my twins
are also cardiologists.

82
00:07:11,133 --> 00:07:13,200
And also...

83
00:07:13,267 --> 00:07:15,567
That necklace...

84
00:07:15,667 --> 00:07:19,900
the pendant I gave you,
the one you dropped.

85
00:07:19,967 --> 00:07:21,933
That was mine.

86
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:26,467
I had two of them.

87
00:07:26,533 --> 00:07:28,700
I'm sure of it.

88
00:07:28,767 --> 00:07:35,000
Because I had them made into two
for you and Olive to keep.

89
00:07:35,067 --> 00:07:41,267
Because I wanted you
to have something from me

90
00:07:41,333 --> 00:07:43,167
before I give you up.

91
00:07:43,233 --> 00:07:46,900
I couldn't provide a good life
for you and Olive.

92
00:07:46,967 --> 00:07:51,333
That's why it was so painful
to write that letter.

93
00:07:57,167 --> 00:08:00,467
Please forgive me, Jade.

94
00:08:00,533 --> 00:08:02,267
I'm sorry, sweetie.

95
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:05,100
Forgive me for giving you up
for adoption

96
00:08:05,167 --> 00:08:06,533
when you were just a baby.

97
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:09,300
Forgive me.

98
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:20,267
I'm sorry.

99
00:08:28,233 --> 00:08:29,300
Here, Mommy.

100
00:08:29,367 --> 00:08:30,700
Have some more.

101
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,467
It's really good!

102
00:08:33,533 --> 00:08:35,633
- Thank you, Mommy.
- This is a good choice.

103
00:09:10,033 --> 00:09:12,867
I'm sorry that I have
to make you sleep

104
00:09:12,933 --> 00:09:14,900
the same way you did
to me before.

105
00:09:16,233 --> 00:09:19,167
What did I do to deserve
such special treatment

106
00:09:19,233 --> 00:09:20,867
from a loving daughter?

107
00:09:24,633 --> 00:09:27,333
I'm gonna get you some juice.

108
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:28,200
Okay.

109
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:36,033
Please don't cry.

110
00:09:37,967 --> 00:09:40,400
I'm not sure how I feel, but...

111
00:09:41,900 --> 00:09:44,933
I can see how much you regret
what you did.

112
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:58,600
I forgive you.

113
00:10:03,533 --> 00:10:09,100
You're not mad at me, sweetie?
Do you forgive me?

114
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:20,333
It's true.

115
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:22,733
Olive is my sister.

116
00:11:01,067 --> 00:11:04,700
I know that you won't be able
to forgive me after this.

117
00:11:04,767 --> 00:11:08,333
But I'm still sorry that I have
to do this.

118
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,300
No one will hear you scream.

119
00:11:18,367 --> 00:11:26,433
I will make sure that you can
never leave me.

120
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:30,133
You will be like a living doll.

121
00:11:31,700 --> 00:11:36,533
My living doll.

122
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,633
You put me through so much pain.

123
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:42,233
I don't deserve to be in pain
and imprisoned in this house.

124
00:11:42,333 --> 00:11:45,033
I want to be free,
I want to be strong,

125
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:46,933
and I want to be happy.

126
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:49,667
With my Mommy Emma.

127
00:11:49,733 --> 00:11:51,300
Goodbye, Mommy.

128
00:12:16,167 --> 00:12:18,133
Wait, what the heck is this?

129
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:21,233
Mom, so they become your
daughters all of a sudden.

130
00:12:22,267 --> 00:12:23,600
Especially Olive.

131
00:12:23,667 --> 00:12:25,400
She put us through a lot
of pain!

132
00:12:25,467 --> 00:12:26,933
She made our family miserable!

133
00:12:28,767 --> 00:12:29,933
Listen, Emma.

134
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:33,433
Listen.

135
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:35,600
I understand.

136
00:12:35,667 --> 00:12:39,967
I am mad about everything
that Olive did to us.

137
00:12:41,233 --> 00:12:41,933
But...

138
00:12:43,233 --> 00:12:48,400
It also frustrates me because,
of all people, why her?

139
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:52,333
But what can I do about it?
Everything is leading to her.

140
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:55,333
Destiny led us to her.

141
00:12:55,400 --> 00:13:00,067
I'm thinking that I'm paying
for my sins.

142
00:13:00,133 --> 00:13:01,667
Olive became the way she is

143
00:13:01,733 --> 00:13:04,567
because I gave them up
for adoption.

144
00:13:04,633 --> 00:13:07,433
I can accept Jade as my sister.

145
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:10,433
But I can never accept Olive!

146
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:13,800
I can't even accept her
as a human being!

147
00:13:13,867 --> 00:13:15,800
She's a human being!

148
00:13:19,233 --> 00:13:21,867
Olive is my daughter!
She's a human being!

149
00:13:23,167 --> 00:13:27,400
Fine! She's a horrible person!
I know that!

150
00:13:27,467 --> 00:13:29,667
But she's my daughter!
She's a human being!

151
00:13:32,767 --> 00:13:36,967
I'm thinking she became the way
she is because of me.

152
00:13:37,033 --> 00:13:39,133
Because I gave them up
for adoption!

153
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:42,733
Perhaps she didn't get
proper care.

154
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:45,800
She didn't experience
motherly love

155
00:13:45,867 --> 00:13:46,900
because I wasn't there for her.

156
00:13:46,967 --> 00:13:50,467
I abandoned her that's why she
turned that way.

157
00:13:50,533 --> 00:13:53,367
So if you hate her,
you should hate me too!

158
00:13:53,433 --> 00:13:55,333
Because I caused all this.

159
00:13:55,433 --> 00:13:57,867
I'm the reason why
this is happening!

160
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:37,600
Caloy, here have some snacks.

161
00:14:37,667 --> 00:14:39,200
Thank you.

162
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:44,367
- Enjoy your snack.
- Thank you.

163
00:15:43,533 --> 00:15:44,967
Emma, sweetie.

164
00:15:47,833 --> 00:15:50,667
I understand.

165
00:15:50,733 --> 00:15:53,933
I know it's hard to accept
that Olive is your sister.

166
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:56,300
But I hope you understand me.

167
00:15:57,933 --> 00:16:00,000
Mom, what about me?

168
00:16:00,067 --> 00:16:02,100
I'm your daughter, too.

169
00:16:02,167 --> 00:16:03,400
Mookie is your granddaughter.

170
00:16:03,467 --> 00:16:05,300
And my daughter's life
is in danger right now

171
00:16:05,367 --> 00:16:07,500
because of her.

172
00:16:07,567 --> 00:16:10,967
I could let it go if she didn't
harm my daughter.

173
00:16:11,067 --> 00:16:13,233
But she abused her!

174
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:15,567
I can never forgive her, Mom.

175
00:16:24,667 --> 00:16:27,733
And you don't have
to forgive her.

176
00:16:43,067 --> 00:16:45,400
You're all my children.

177
00:16:45,467 --> 00:16:47,733
I love you all so much.

178
00:17:28,067 --> 00:17:29,733
What should I do now?

179
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:32,933
I have to be brave.

180
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,933
I have to be strong.

181
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:10,267
Emma, I wish someday you and
your siblings would get along.

182
00:18:28,967 --> 00:18:30,633
Don't worry.

183
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:34,300
I'm nothing like Olive.

184
00:18:34,367 --> 00:18:36,467
I will never hurt you...

185
00:18:38,100 --> 00:18:41,933
And I will help you find her
and Mookie.

186
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:43,500
I promise.

187
00:19:19,467 --> 00:19:22,400
I think I know where we can find
them.

188
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:27,400
I remember our dad had
a rest house before.

189
00:19:28,833 --> 00:19:31,800
We fought and made up there.

190
00:19:31,867 --> 00:19:33,567
She could have brought Mookie
there.

191
00:19:36,900 --> 00:19:38,333
What are we waiting for then?
Let's go save Mookie.

192
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:39,767
Come on, let's go.

193
00:19:51,767 --> 00:19:53,267
Where are you going?

194
00:19:54,833 --> 00:19:57,200
Did you put something
on my food?

195
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:04,633
After all that I've done
for you.

196
00:20:07,033 --> 00:20:09,233
This is how you're going
to repay me?

197
00:20:14,300 --> 00:20:16,233
You're leaving me again?

198
00:20:18,133 --> 00:20:19,433
You're trying to escape?

199
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:22,533
Mommy...

200
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:24,200
Don't you dare call me Mommy!

201
00:20:25,633 --> 00:20:27,067
You betrayed me!

202
00:20:31,067 --> 00:20:32,967
You poisoned me!

203
00:20:36,833 --> 00:20:38,767
I trusted you.

204
00:20:40,933 --> 00:20:44,600
I believed you when you said you
chose to be with me.

205
00:20:46,333 --> 00:20:47,367
Mommy, you're hurting me.

206
00:20:47,433 --> 00:20:49,733
I thought you loved me more than
Emma!

207
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:53,433
But you lied to me over and over
again!

208
00:20:53,500 --> 00:20:54,400
Stop it!

209
00:20:56,333 --> 00:20:58,467
You can never hurt me again!

210
00:20:58,533 --> 00:21:00,867
I am no longer weak!

211
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:05,367
- Olive?
- Mookie, sweetie!

212
00:21:05,433 --> 00:21:07,533
- Mookie?
- Mookie, Olive!

213
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:09,200
Wait, the door!

214
00:21:09,300 --> 00:21:11,400
- Dan. Open it, hurry.
- Let me get it.

215
00:21:15,867 --> 00:21:16,833
It won't open.

216
00:21:16,900 --> 00:21:19,633
- I'm leaving this place.
- Mookie, no.

217
00:21:19,700 --> 00:21:20,867
Let go, Mommy!

218
00:21:20,933 --> 00:21:23,067
Mookie, please. Don't leave me!

219
00:21:23,133 --> 00:21:25,367
You said you want things
back to how they were before.

220
00:21:25,433 --> 00:21:27,833
- Just the two of us.
- Mommy, no!

221
00:21:27,900 --> 00:21:29,633
I'm not letting you go.

222
00:21:29,700 --> 00:21:32,867
No, no, no, Mookie.

223
00:21:32,933 --> 00:21:34,633
No!

224
00:21:36,100 --> 00:21:38,100
- There.
- Let's go, come on!

225
00:21:38,167 --> 00:21:39,067
- Hurry.
- Mookie!

226
00:21:40,467 --> 00:21:41,767
- Mookie!
- Olive?

227
00:21:41,867 --> 00:21:44,833
- Mookie!
- Mookie, sweetie.

228
00:21:54,033 --> 00:21:57,667
Caloy, please. I want to leave!
Please!

229
00:21:59,900 --> 00:22:05,767
A disobedient brat like you
deserves to be punished!

230
00:22:05,833 --> 00:22:08,367
- Lock her up in her room.
- No, no!

231
00:22:08,433 --> 00:22:10,667
No! Stop it!

232
00:22:10,733 --> 00:22:13,700
Mommy, stop this, let me go!

233
00:22:13,767 --> 00:22:14,833
Mommy!

234
00:22:18,033 --> 00:22:19,900
Mommy!

235
00:22:22,267 --> 00:22:24,800
You're a horrible person!
You're cruel!

236
00:22:24,867 --> 00:22:28,700
I don't want you as my mom!
I wish you were not my mother!

237
00:22:28,767 --> 00:22:34,933
You! It's you! You're insane!
You deserved to be alone!

238
00:22:43,300 --> 00:22:45,000
Based on your report,

239
00:22:45,067 --> 00:22:48,433
you can file a case of
kidnapping, child abuse,

240
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:51,100
physical injury, and frustrated
murder against the suspect.

241
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:54,500
Ma'am, would Olive be sent
to prison

242
00:22:54,567 --> 00:22:56,933
if she were to face all those
cases against her?

243
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:58,200
Yes.

244
00:22:58,267 --> 00:23:00,467
I need you to get me more
Canixidol.

245
00:23:01,833 --> 00:23:04,067
Wait, what is that?

246
00:23:04,133 --> 00:23:05,600
What's this?

247
00:23:05,667 --> 00:23:07,733
Are you going to use this
on my child?

248
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:09,233
You're being paranoid.
Give that back.

249
00:23:09,300 --> 00:23:10,500
- Ouch!
- Emma!

250
00:23:10,567 --> 00:23:11,867
Relax, Mookie.

251
00:23:13,100 --> 00:23:16,067
I'm just preparing for our trip
to heaven.

252
00:23:16,133 --> 00:23:18,367
You don't want us to go
to heaven.

253
00:23:20,333 --> 00:23:22,900
You want us to go to hell!
